@startuml fig-tls-13
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title TLS 1.3 Handshake (1-RTT)

participant "Client" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server" as S #C8E6C9

== TCP Connection (already established) ==

C -[#1565C0]> S : **ClientHello**\nSupported cipher suites\nKey share (ECDHE public key)\nSupported versions

S -[#1565C0]> C : **ServerHello**\nChosen cipher suite\nKey share (server public key)

note over C, S #E1BEE7
  Both sides compute the shared secret
  (Diffie–Hellman key exchange)
  All subsequent messages are encrypted
end note

S -[#43A047]> C : {EncryptedExtensions}\n{Certificate}\n{CertificateVerify}\n{Finished}

C -[#43A047]> S : {Finished}

== APPLICATION DATA (encrypted) ==

C <-[#333333]> S : Encrypted application data

legend right
  TLS 1.3 completes in a single round trip.
  The key exchange uses ephemeral
  Diffie–Hellman (no RSA key transport).
  Curly braces {} denote encrypted messages.
  Resumption allows 0-RTT in subsequent
  connections (with replay risk).
endlegend
@enduml
